### Try-Catch Blocks

Try-catch blocks allow you to handle exceptions gracefully without crashing the program.

---

### Basic Syntax

```cpp
try {
  // Code that might throw
} catch (ExceptionType1& e) {
  // Handle ExceptionType1
} catch (ExceptionType2& e) {
  // Handle ExceptionType2
} catch (...) {
  // Catch-all handler
}
```

---

### Multiple Catch Blocks

```cpp
try {
  // Some code
} catch (const std::out_of_range& e) {
  cout << "Out of range: " << e.what();
} catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
  cout << "Runtime error: " << e.what();
} catch (const std::exception& e) {
  cout << "General exception: " << e.what();
}
```

---

### Catch-All Handler

```cpp
try {
  // Risky code
} catch (...) {
  cout << "An unknown exception occurred";
  throw;  // Re-throw after logging
}
```

---

### Exception Specification (Deprecated)

```cpp
// Old style (deprecated in C++11, removed in C++17)
void func() throw(int, string);

// Modern C++
void func() noexcept;         // Never throws
void func() noexcept(false);  // May throw
```

---

### Function Try Block

```cpp
int riskyFunc() try {
  // Function body
  return 42;
} catch (const std::exception& e) {
  cout << "Error in riskyFunc: " << e.what();
  throw;  // Re-throw
}
```

---

> **Key Point:** Order catch blocks from most specific to most general. The base class `std::exception` should be caught last. Always catch by const reference to avoid slicing.

codeExample:
#include <iostream>
#include <stdexcept>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  try {
    int age;
    cout << "Enter age: ";
    cin >> age;

    if (age < 0) {
      throw invalid_argument("Age cannot be negative");
    }
    if (age > 150) {
      throw out_of_range("Age exceeds reasonable limit");
    }

    cout << "Age is valid: " << age << endl;
  } catch (const invalid_argument& e) {
    cout << "Invalid: " << e.what() << endl;
  } catch (const out_of_range& e) {
    cout << "Out of range: " << e.what() << endl;
  } catch (const exception& e) {
    cout << "Error: " << e.what() << endl;
  }
  return 0;
}
